<br>
I wear a Robe of Living Fungus, which has 10FR, as well as 10AC and 12STA.<br>
Golden Daimond Mask I also wear for resists, but it only has 3MR.<br>
Blue diamond gear is very nice, but expensive.<br>
Oh, and consider upgrading your cloak to Shimmering Terror Hide Cloak, 50hp is very nice on a back item <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> Do you have a haste item?  Silver Chitin Hand Wraps have 3 to all resists, and ... haste <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :lol --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/laugh.gif ALT=":lol"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p>-Korph
<br>
<br>
<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=308735"><img src="http://gjband.com/Sig.jpg"><br>Level 51 Disciple</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uscaliagluon.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Scalia Gluon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Monk-in-Training</span><br>  Posts: 78<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(9/27/02 1:08:41 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=11625.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: I troubles against caster class mobs</span><hr size=1> Casters are usually harder than non-casters, especially for soloing melees. Doubly so for Monks since they break FD and we have no half-way reliable way of interrupting them. Casters were made even more dangerous a couple of patches back because of the resist changes.<br>
<br>
That said, your armor is decent for the level. Your biggest problem is that you don't have a source of haste and that your weapons are beginning to show their age. I'd go farm CC (Orcs are still mostly light blue at 41) and get a couple of KDs and at least a FBSS or, better yet, SCHW.<br>
<br>
A Froggy Crown would also be nice, not only for resists, but also because it's a better headpiece than what you are wearing. STR and expecially DEX have minimal effect on Monks, but AC and especially HP are huge. <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=71792 target=_blank>Scalia</a> /  <a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=71783 target =_blank>Gluon</a> on E'ci</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#778899><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/udalarianwashere.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dalarian was here</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Monk-in-Training</span><br>  Posts: 96<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(9/27/02 1:37:45 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=11625.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Cheap +5 to all resists</span><hr size=1> Kaladim Constitutional<br>
<br>
+5 to all resists and maybe something else, +5 sta or something, can't remember.<br>
<br>
Anyways, buy one (1), should run you around 30p in the bazaar. Then, get in the habit of 'force' drinking whatever you're using for drink, IE putting it into an open inventory slot and using it like a potion/alcohol. Do it until you get a 'you can't drink anything else, you'd explode!' message. Keep the Kaladim Constitutional above all your other drinkables, and *bam*, indefinate +5 to all resists for 30p. Until you forget to force drink and drink it on accident. =p<br>
<br>
*runs off to the bazaar to buy another Kaladim Constitutional and Centi Steaks* <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ukokueiakujin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kokuei Akujin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Monk</span><br>  Posts: 110<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(9/27/02 2:06:26 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=11625.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Cheap +5 to all resists</span><hr size=1>  Self buffed I'm at 72svm 104svf and 87svc <br>
<br>
